'''Misaki''' ({{lang-ja|御先}}, "misaki") are a collective term for spirit-like existences in Japan like [[god]]s, [[demon]]s and spirits, among other supernatural entities. Their name comes from a [[kannushi]]'s vanguard.<ref name="sakurai">{{Cite book|author=桜井徳太郎編|title=民間信仰辞典|year=1980|publisher=東京堂出版|isbn=978-4-490-10137-9|pages=276–277頁}}</ref>

== Summary ==
