{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q7607372]] Wikidata name: Misaki [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 08:12, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{short description|Collective term for divine spirits in Japan}} {{About|misaki as divine spirits}} '''Misaki''' ({{lang-ja|御先}}, "misaki") are a collective term for spirit-like existences in Japan like [[:en:God|God]]s, [[:en:Demon|Demon]]s and spirits, among other supernatural entities. Their name comes from a [[kannushi]]'s vanguard.<ref name="sakurai">{{Cite book|author=桜井徳太郎編|title=民間信仰辞典|year=1980|publisher=東京堂出版|isbn=978-4-490-10137-9|pages=276–277頁}}</ref>
